    <!-- Custom Scrollable Menu Guide:
        How to Add a New Page (e.g., LorePage3):
        1. Content Area: Under LorePagesContainer, copy LorePage2 and rename it to LorePage3.
           - Update ItemList name to LoreList3.
           - Adjust content (StaticText, StaticImage) as needed.
           - For StaticText items:
             - Set origin x to -1000, align="l".
             - Space normal lines (header_4) 50 pixels apart in y-direction (e.g., y = 440, next at y = 390).
             - Space headers (header_3) 100 pixels apart from the next line (e.g., header at y = 190, next line at y = 90).
           Example for LorePage3:
           <Item name="LorePage3" origin="0 0" hidden="true">
               <ItemList name="LoreList3" align="c" origin="0 0" direction="y" sizeX="2300" sizeY="1180" clipChildren="true">
                   <ButtonGraphics align="r" origin="40 0">
                       <RenderObject2D texture="data/textures/gui/square.tga" sizeX="32" sizeY="64" color="f97b0340"/>
                       <OnHover><RenderObject2D texture="data/textures/gui/square.tga" sizeX="32" sizeY="64" color="f97b03ff"/></OnHover>
                       <OnClick><RenderObject2D texture="data/textures/gui/square.tga" sizeX="32" sizeY="64" color="f97b03ff"/></OnClick>
                   </ButtonGraphics>
                   <StaticImage origin="0 540" sizeY="70">
                       <RenderObject2D texture="data/textures/gui/square.tga" sizeX="2300" sizeY="70" color="00000050"/>
                       <StaticText text="Episode 3: New Page" font="header_3" textColor="f97b03" align="l"/>
                   </StaticImage>
                   <Item origin="-1000 440"><StaticText text="Line 1 of new page." font="header_4" textColor="f0e3cc" align="l"/></Item>
                   <Item origin="-1000 390"><StaticText text="Line 2 of new page." font="header_4" textColor="f0e3cc" align="l"/></Item>
               </ItemList>
           </Item>
        2. Navigation Bar: Under PageNavigationList, copy Page2Button and rename it to Page3Button.
           - Update text to "3".
           - Set origin y = previous button's y - 50 (e.g., Page2Button at y = 450, so Page3Button at y = 400).
           - Update OnClick to hide all other pages and show LorePage3.
           Example for Page3Button:
           <Button name="Page3Button" sizeX="60" sizeY="40" origin="0 400">
               <ButtonText origin="0 0" text="3" font="header_3" textColor="f0e3cc"/>
               <OnHover>
                   <RenderObject2D texture="data/textures/gui/button_hover_01.tga" color="f97b03" sizeX="60" sizeY="40"/>
                   <ButtonText origin="0 0" text="3" font="header_3" textColor="211e1d"/>
               </OnHover>
               <OnClick>
                   <RenderObject2D texture="data/textures/gui/button_hover_01.tga" color="40392b" sizeX="60" sizeY="40"/>
                   <Action type="Hide" target="LorePage1"/>
                   <Action type="Hide" target="LorePage2"/>
                   <Action type="Show" target="LorePage3"/>
               </OnClick>
           </Button>
           - Update existing buttons' OnClick to hide LorePage3:
             Page1Button: Add <Action type="Hide" target="LorePage3"/> before <Action type="Show" target="LorePage1"/>.
             Page2Button: Add <Action type="Hide" target="LorePage3"/> before <Action type="Show" target="LorePage2"/>.
        3. OnOpen/OnClose Events: In Custom_Scrollable_Menu, add hide actions for LorePage3.
           Example:
           <OnOpen>
               <Action type="TriggerEvent" target="GUI_CAPTURE_INPUT"/>
               <Action type="Hide" target="LorePage1"/>
               <Action type="Hide" target="LorePage2"/>
               <Action type="Hide" target="LorePage3"/>
           </OnOpen>
           <OnClose>
               <Action type="TriggerEvent" target="GUI_RELEASE_INPUT"/>
               <Action type="Hide" target="LorePage1"/>
               <Action type="Hide" target="LorePage2"/>
               <Action type="Hide" target="LorePage3"/>
           </OnClose>
        4. Dummy Item: Update the dummy item's origin y to last button's y - 100 (e.g., Page3Button at y = 400, so dummy item at y = 300).
           Example:
           <Item origin="0 300">
               <StaticText text="" font="header_4" textColor="f0e3cc"/>
           </Item>
    -->

